\"hey, are you watching the super bowl?\" And of course I told him the truth, \"no\".\n\nYou should have seen the genuine look of shock and horror in this man's eyes when I told him that. He looked at me like I had a disease or something.\n\nShocking reminder that these people still exist and that I used to be one. All things considered, I'm grateful for the outlook that I have in life. And there's no going back for me. In fact I'd rather die than go back to that. \n\nThat is all.", "author": "kek-is-tan", "created": 1770769646730, "profile_picture": "I8XXB1DBtIOB", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Trump454748", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Have you ever had an encounter with a normie that was just an obscene reminder of how it used to be living inside the Matrix and how long you've been out for?", "last_comment_created": 1770810828408, "content": "<p>So I met a new neighbor last Sunday. Nice guy. Nice family. Things were going well, we had some common interests and experiences. But lo and behold, he asked me the question, &quot;hey, are you watching the super bowl?&quot; And of course I told him the truth, &quot;no&quot;.</p>\n<p>You should have seen the genuine look of shock and horror in this man's eyes when I told him that. He looked at me like I had a disease or something.</p>\n<p>Shocking reminder that these people still exist and that I used to be one. All things considered, I'm grateful for the outlook that I have in life. And there's no going back for me. In fact I'd rather die than go back to that.</p>\n<p>That is all.</p>\n", "score_down": 3, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 44, "sc